## Getting Started

### Prerequisites

- Go 1.18 or higher
{{if eq .Config.Database "PostgreSQL"}}
- PostgreSQL
{{else if eq .Config.Database "MongoDB"}}
- MongoDB
{{else if eq .Config.Database "MySQL"}}
- MySQL
{{else if eq .Config.Database "SQLite"}}
- SQLite
{{end}}
{{if (HasFeature "Redis Caching")}}
- Redis
{{end}}
{{if ne .Config.Docker "None"}}
- Docker and Docker Compose
{{end}}

### Running the API

1. Clone the repository

```bash
git clone <your-repo-url>
cd {{ .Config.ProjectName }}
```

2. Install dependencies

```bash
go mod download
```

{{if eq .Config.Docker "Full (development + production)" "Development only"}}
3. Start the development environment with Docker

```bash
make docker-up
```

4. Run the API

```bash
make run
```
{{else}}
3. Run the API

```bash
make run
```
{{end}}

The GraphQL playground will be available at http://localhost:8080

### Build for Production

```bash
make build
```

The compiled binary will be in the `bin` directory.

## Project Structure

```
.
├── cmd/
│   └── server/           # API server entry point
├── config/               # Configuration management
├── db/                   # Database migrations and models
├── graph/                # GraphQL specific code
│   ├── generated/        # Auto-generated GraphQL code
│   ├── resolvers/        # Your GraphQL resolvers
│   ├── model/            # GraphQL models
│   └── schema/           # GraphQL schema definition
├── internal/             # Business logic
│   ├── auth/             # Authentication logic
│   ├── models/           # Database models
│   └── services/         # Business services
└── pkg/                  # Reusable packages
```

